{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1124281c-3f3d-4e4e-a9d9-e42e54eb8b52","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but with important caveats:\n\n**Problems with your current targets:**\n\n1. **`net5.0`** — Not supported. .NET 5 is out of support and MSTest v3 targets `net6.0` as the minimum modern TFM. You'd need to upgrade to `net6.0` or later.\n\n2. **`netcoreapp3.1`** — Not supported. MSTest v3 dropped support for .NET Core 3.1. You'd need `net6.0`+.\n\n3. **`net462`** — This one is fine. MSTest v3 still supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+.\n\n**Migration steps:**\n\n- Replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` (or `net8.0` for current LTS).\n- Update packages to the MSTest v3 meta-package (`MSTest` instead of separate `TestFramework`/`TestAdapter` references).\n- Review any use of deprecated APIs (e.g., `Assert.That` namespace changes, `DeploymentItem` behavior).\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ef7b0db7-1f86-403e-875f-c1a101a9ee2a","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"B80E:28893:EB06CF:F8C0DE:6A044DFE"},"id":"c594bf06-a814-4df1-bdf1-087f8b7197f5","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:10:20.122Z","parentId":"5bd26202-e3e4-4980-8256-f7296e49f737"}
